data.chText: 当局发出了逮捕她的令状。
data.enText: They issued a warrant for her arrest.

an acceptable reason for doing sth

data.chText: 进一步调查显然是必要的。
这种情况很难证明解雇他们是正当的。
data.enText: The situation scarcely warrants their/them being dismissed.

means: (接受款项、服务等的)凭单，许可证

data.chText: 我给你打保票；我向你保证
data.enText: used to tell sb that you are sure of sth and that they can be sure of it too

tr: a writ from a court commanding police to perform specified acts
a written assurance that some product or service will be provided or will meet certain specifications

example: a Democrat usually gets the union's endorsement

tr: a type of security issued by a corporation (usually together with a bond or preferred stock) that gives the holder the right to purchase a certain amount of common stock at a stated price
example: as a sweetener they offered warrants along with the fixed-income securities

tr: stand behind and guarantee the quality, accuracy, or condition of
example: The dealer warrants all the cars he sells

tr: show to be reasonable or provide adequate ground for
example: The emergency does not warrant all of us buying guns

value.def: If something warrants a particular action, it makes the action seem necessary or appropriate for the circumstances.

example.ex: The allegations are serious enough to warrant an investigation...
example.tran: 这些指控很严重，有必要进行一番调查。

example.ex: No matter was too small to warrant his attention.
example.tran: 再小的事也会引起他的注意。

example.ex: Do you think this fear is warranted?
example.tran: 你认为有必要这样害怕吗？

value.def: A warrant is a legal document that allows someone to do something, especially one that is signed by a judge or magistrate and gives the police permission to arrest someone or search their house.

example.ex: Police confirmed that they had issued a warrant for his arrest.
example.tran: 警方证实他们已经签发了对他的拘捕令。
设备已经按照令状分配好了。

value.def: If you say that there is no warrant for something, you mean that there is no good reason to justify it.

example.ex: There is some warrant for holding back on full-scale aid.
example.tran: 有理由不进行全面援助。

gramarinfo.label: oft with brd-neg, usu N <l>for</l> n/-ing

value.def: If you warrant that something is true or will happen, you say officially that it is true, or guarantee that it will happen.

example.ex: All entrants must warrant that their entry is entirely their own work...
example.tran: 所有参赛者必须保证其参赛作品完全是自己创作的。

example.ex: The contract warrants that an experienced person is on board all the time.
example.tran: 合同确保一位富有经验的人会一直呆在船上。
